import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['Miles_per_Gallon'], bins=20, color='green', alpha=0.8)
    plt.axvline(data['Miles_per_Gallon'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    plt.axvline(data['Miles_per_Gallon'].median(), color='blue', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median')
    plt.xlabel('Miles_per_Gallon')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Miles_per_Gallon?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[['Acceleration', 'Cylinders']]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 6))
    ax.boxplot([data[data['Cylinders'] == 3]['Acceleration'], 
                data[data['Cylinders'] == 4]['Acceleration'], 
                data[data['Cylinders'] == 5]['Acceleration'], 
                data[data['Cylinders'] == 6]['Acceleration'], 
                data[data['Cylinders'] == 8]['Acceleration']], 
               labels=['3', '4', '5', '6', '8'])
    ax.set_xlabel('Cylinders')
    ax.set_ylabel('Acceleration')
    ax.set_title('How does Acceleration relate to Cylinders?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
